cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.PL

The paper discusses the issue of password storage and security, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The study also involves computer science students and their approach to password storage, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential consequences of insecure password storage, which relates to cybercrime (cs.CY) and programming languages (cs.PL) as developers must write secure code to prevent such attacks.
